reviews.review_text:
12-30-1981 
The "first set" portion of this one off show features some outstanding playing by the boys.  From Jack Straw to Lazy Lightning you get top shelf playing, particularly from Garcia...the mix is good, slightly Brent heavy...TLEO is more than solid, Dire Wolf is very well done and Rooster is phenomenal (check out Weir's tasteful, yes tasteful, slide playing that Garcia picks up and shreds...) Cumberland is at it's jangly and cherry picking best...the Lighting jam rips...highly recommeded listen...
